snippet: Caught up on all your favorite programs? Then perhaps it’s time to sample four Shows You Didn’t Know Existed.
abstract: Neil Genzlinger Critic's Notebook highlights four 'Shows You Didn't Know Existed,' to get television viewers through lull until new fall series arrive; shows include BBC America's Nature's Weirdest, Going Deep With David Rees on National Geographic Channel, Low Budget Sketch Show from Upright Citizens Brigade Theater, and Bravo's Extreme Guide to Parenting.
lead_paragraph: Caught up on all your favorite programs? Then perhaps it’s time to sample four Shows You Didn’t Know Existed.
